3. C++ <-> WPF Interfacing
You have a few options:

C++/CLI wrapper DLL:

Wrap your native engine C++ classes in managed classes.

WPF (C#) can call them directly.

Pros: Tight integration, single process.

Cons: Mixed managed/unmanaged adds complexity.

Native DLL + P/Invoke:

Expose engine functions as plain C functions.

WPF calls them via DllImport.

Pros: Simple, clean separation.

Cons: Data marshalling needed (meshes, arrays).

IPC / Networking:

Engine runs as a separate process.

WPF talks via TCP/UDP or shared memory.

Pros: Totally decoupled, engine crashes won’t crash UI.

Cons: Slight latency, more complex messaging.

